<section>
  <p>
  This site demonstrates <a href="https://github.com/philhawksworth/netlify-plugin-add-instagram">netlify-plugin-add-instagram</a>, a <a href="https://docs.netlify.com/configure-builds/build-plugins/?{{ site.utm }}">Build plugin</a> for <a href="https://netlify.com?{{ site.utm }}">Netlify</a>. The code for this site in available in on <a href="{{ pkg.repository.url }}">GitHub</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    When this site is builds, the build plugin requests (and caches for future builds) data and image assets from Instagram. those images can then be served as part of this site. Subsequent build get available image assets from the build cache.
  </p>
</section>

